# Local Claude Code directory (personal, per-machine — never shared by default).
# Default-deny rather than naming settings.local.json alone: a single-filename
# rule only protects the exact file named today, not whatever Claude Code or a
# tool creates under .claude/ tomorrow (launch.json, mcp.json, a cache, a
# session log) — and this repo's own content-safety scan in
# scripts/validate-marketplace.mjs only walks plugins/, so nothing dropped
# here would ever be caught by it. Un-ignore explicitly (!.claude/whatever) if
# the team ever wants a specific file shared project-wide.
.claude/*
